ools and my binding javascript is loaded or not. This has the benefit of a slightly faster-loading site as the 2 scripts won&#8217;t be loaded if unneeded, and hopefully will help [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>This post first appeared on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://arconixpc.com">Arconix Computers - Web Design and Technology Services for RI, MA and CT</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"John";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:867:"<p>I released a new version of the <a href="http://arcnx.co/as">Arconix Shortcodes</a> plugin over the weekend. This update adds a global flag that controls whether the <a href="http://flowplayer.org/tools/">jQuery Tools</a> and my binding javascript is loaded or not. This has the benefit of a slightly faster-loading site as the 2 scripts won&#8217;t be loaded if unneeded, and hopefully will help minimize javascript conflicts by keeping those scripts as separate as possible. As always, report bugs and request new features in the <a href="http://wordpress.org/tags/arconix-shortcodes?forum_id=10">WordPress forum</a> or <a title="Contact" href="http://arconixpc.com/contact">contact me</a> directly.</p>\n<p>This post first appeared on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://arconixpc.com">Arconix Computers - Web Design and Technology Services for RI, MA and CT</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:54:"http://arconixpc.com/2011/arconix-shortcodes-v092/feed";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/sla